{"thig16.1":{"thig16.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 16.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 16.1 ","html":"<article id='thig16.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig16.1:0.2":{"pli":"Mahānipāta ","eng":"The Great Book ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig16.1:0.3":{"pli":"Sumedhātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sumedhā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig16.1:1.1":{"pli":"Mantāvatiyā nagare, ","eng":"In Mantāvatī city, Sumedhā, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:1.2":{"pli":"Rañño koñcassa aggamahesiyā; ","eng":"the daughter of King Koñca’s chief queen, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:1.3":{"pli":"Dhītā āsiṃ sumedhā, ","eng":"was converted by those ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:1.4":{"pli":"Pasāditā sāsanakarehi. ","eng":"who practice the Buddha’s teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:2.1":{"pli":"Sīlavatī cittakathā, ","eng":"She was virtuous, a brilliant speaker, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:2.2":{"pli":"Bahussutā buddhasāsane vinitā; ","eng":"learned, and trained in the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:2.3":{"pli":"Mātāpitaro upagamma, ","eng":"She went up to her mother and father and said: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:2.4":{"pli":"Bhaṇati “ubhayo nisāmetha. ","eng":"“Pay heed, both of you! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:3.1":{"pli":"Nibbānābhiratāhaṃ, ","eng":"I delight in extinguishment! ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:3.2":{"pli":"Asassataṃ bhavagataṃ yadipi dibbaṃ; ","eng":"No state of life is eternal, not even that of the gods; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"She uses the term <i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhavagata</i> (“state of life”) seven times. It is not found elsewhere in early Pali, only once in the late <a href='index.html?q=pe5#72.2'>Pe 5:72.2</a>. "},"thig16.1:3.3":{"pli":"Kimaṅgaṃ pana tucchā kāmā, ","eng":"what then of sensual pleasures, so hollow, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:3.4":{"pli":"Appassādā bahuvighātā. ","eng":"offering little gratification and much distress. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:4.1":{"pli":"Kāmā kaṭukā āsī, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are bitter as the venom of a snake, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:4.2":{"pli":"Visūpamā yesu mucchitā bālā; ","eng":"yet fools are infatuated by them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:4.3":{"pli":"Te dīgharattaṃ niraye, ","eng":"Sent to hell for a very long time, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:4.4":{"pli":"Samappitā haññante dukkhitā. ","eng":"they are beaten and tortured. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:5.1":{"pli":"Socanti pāpakammā, ","eng":"Those who grow in wickedness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:5.2":{"pli":"Vinipāte pāpavaddhino sadā; ","eng":"ever lament in the underworld <j>due to their own bad deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:5.3":{"pli":"Kāyena ca vācāya ca, ","eng":"They’re fools, unrestrained in body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:5.4":{"pli":"Manasā ca asaṃvutā bālā. ","eng":"mind, and speech. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:6.1":{"pli":"Bālā te duppaññā, ","eng":"Those witless, senseless fools, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:6.2":{"pli":"Acetanā dukkhasamudayoruddhā; ","eng":"trapped by the origin of suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:6.3":{"pli":"Desente ajānantā, ","eng":"are ignorant, not understanding the noble truths ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:6.4":{"pli":"Na bujjhare ariyasaccāni. ","eng":"when they are being taught. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:7.1":{"pli":"Saccāni amma buddhavaradesitāni, ","eng":"Most people, mum, ignorant of the truths ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:7.2":{"pli":"Te bahutarā ajānantā ye; ","eng":"taught by the excellent Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:7.3":{"pli":"Abhinandanti bhavagataṃ, ","eng":"look forward to a state of life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:7.4":{"pli":"Pihenti devesu upapattiṃ. ","eng":"longing for rebirth among the gods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:8.1":{"pli":"Devesupi upapatti, ","eng":"Yet even rebirth among the gods ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:8.2":{"pli":"Asassatā bhavagate aniccamhi; ","eng":"in an impermanent state of life is not eternal. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:8.3":{"pli":"Na ca santasanti bālā, ","eng":"But fools are not scared ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:8.4":{"pli":"Punappunaṃ jāyitabbassa. ","eng":"of being reborn time and again. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:9.1":{"pli":"Cattāro vinipātā, ","eng":"Four lower realms and two other realms ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:9.2":{"pli":"Duve ca gatiyo kathañci labbhanti; ","eng":"may be gained somehow or other. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:9.3":{"pli":"Na ca vinipātagatānaṃ, ","eng":"But for those who end up in a lower realm, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:9.4":{"pli":"Pabbajjā atthi nirayesu. ","eng":"there is no way to go forth in the hells. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:10.1":{"pli":"Anujānātha maṃ ubhayo, ","eng":"May you both grant me permission to go forth ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:10.2":{"pli":"Pabbajituṃ dasabalassa pāvacane; ","eng":"in the dispensation of him of the ten powers. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:10.3":{"pli":"Appossukkā ghaṭissaṃ, ","eng":"Living at ease, I shall apply myself ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:10.4":{"pli":"Jātimaraṇappahānāya. ","eng":"to giving up rebirth and death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:11.1":{"pli":"Kiṃ bhavagate abhinanditena, ","eng":"Why look forward to a new state of life ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:11.2":{"pli":"Kāyakalinā asārena; ","eng":"in this useless, insubstantial body? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:11.3":{"pli":"Bhavataṇhāya nirodhā, ","eng":"Grant me permission, I shall go forth ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:11.4":{"pli":"Anujānātha pabbajissāmi. ","eng":"to make an end of craving for a new life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:12.1":{"pli":"Buddhānaṃ uppādo vivajjito, ","eng":"A Buddha has arisen, the time has come, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:12.2":{"pli":"Akkhaṇo khaṇo laddho; ","eng":"the unlucky moment has passed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:12.3":{"pli":"Sīlāni brahmacariyaṃ, ","eng":"As long as I live I’ll never betray ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:12.4":{"pli":"Yāvajīvaṃ na dūseyyaṃ”. ","eng":"my ethical precepts or my chaste path.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:13.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ bhaṇati sumedhā, ","eng":"Then Sumedhā said to her parents: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:13.2":{"pli":"Mātāpitaro “na tāva āhāraṃ; ","eng":"“So long as I remain a layperson, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:13.3":{"pli":"Āharissaṃ gahaṭṭhā, ","eng":"I’ll refuse to eat any food, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:13.4":{"pli":"Maraṇavasaṃ gatāva hessāmi”. ","eng":"until I’ve fallen under the sway of death.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:14.1":{"pli":"Mātā dukkhitā rodati pitā ca, ","eng":"Upset, her mother burst into tears, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:14.2":{"pli":"Assā sabbaso samabhihato; ","eng":"while her father, though grieved, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:14.3":{"pli":"Ghaṭenti saññāpetuṃ, ","eng":"tried his best to persuade her ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:14.4":{"pli":"Pāsādatale chamāpatitaṃ. ","eng":"as she lay collapsed upstairs in the longhouse. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:15.1":{"pli":"“Uṭṭhehi puttaka kiṃ soci, ","eng":"“Get up child, why do you grieve so? ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:15.2":{"pli":"Tena dinnāsi vāraṇavatimhi; ","eng":"You’re already betrothed to be married! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:15.3":{"pli":"Rājā anīkaratto, ","eng":"King Anīkaratta the handsome ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:15.4":{"pli":"Abhirūpo tassa tvaṃ dinnā. ","eng":"is in Vāraṇavatī: he is your betrothed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:16.1":{"pli":"Aggamahesī bhavissasi, ","eng":"You shall be the chief queen, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:16.2":{"pli":"Anikarattassa rājino bhariyā; ","eng":"wife of King Anīkaratta. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:16.3":{"pli":"Sīlāni brahmacariyaṃ, ","eng":"Ethical precepts, the chaste path—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:16.4":{"pli":"Pabbajjā dukkarā puttaka. ","eng":"going forth is hard to do, my child. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:17.1":{"pli":"Rajje āṇā dhanamissariyaṃ, ","eng":"As a royal there is command, wealth, authority, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:17.2":{"pli":"Bhogā sukhā daharikāsi; ","eng":"and the happiness of possessions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:17.3":{"pli":"Bhuñjāhi kāmabhoge, ","eng":"Enjoy sensual pleasures while you’re still young! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:17.4":{"pli":"Vāreyyaṃ hotu te putta”. ","eng":"Let your wedding take place, my child!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:18.1":{"pli":"Atha ne bhaṇati sumedhā, ","eng":"Then Sumedhā said to him: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:18.2":{"pli":"“Mā edisikāni bhavagatamasāraṃ; ","eng":"“Let this not come to pass! Existence is hollow! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:18.3":{"pli":"Pabbajjā vā hohiti, ","eng":"I shall either go forth or die, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:18.4":{"pli":"Maraṇaṃ vā me na ceva vāreyyaṃ. ","eng":"but I shall never marry. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:19.1":{"pli":"Kimiva pūtikāyamasuciṃ, ","eng":"Why cling to this rotting body so foul, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:19.2":{"pli":"Savanagandhaṃ bhayānakaṃ kuṇapaṃ; ","eng":"stinking of fluids, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:19.3":{"pli":"Abhisaṃviseyyaṃ bhastaṃ, ","eng":"a horrifying water-bag carcass, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:19.4":{"pli":"Asakiṃ paggharitaṃ asucipuṇṇaṃ. ","eng":"always oozing, full of filth? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:20.1":{"pli":"Kimiva tahaṃ jānantī, ","eng":"Knowing it like I do, what’s the point? ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:20.2":{"pli":"Vikūlakaṃ maṃsasoṇitupalittaṃ; ","eng":"A carcass is vile, smeared with flesh and blood, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:20.3":{"pli":"Kimikulālayaṃ sakuṇabhattaṃ, ","eng":"food for birds and swarms of worms—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:20.4":{"pli":"Kaḷevaraṃ kissa diyyati. ","eng":"why have we been given it? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:21.1":{"pli":"Nibbuyhati susānaṃ, ","eng":"Before long the body, bereft of consciousness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:21.2":{"pli":"Aciraṃ kāyo apetaviññāṇo; ","eng":"is carried out to the charnel ground, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:21.3":{"pli":"Chuddho kaḷiṅgaraṃ viya, ","eng":"to be discarded like an old log ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:21.4":{"pli":"Jigucchamānehi ñātīhi. ","eng":"by relatives in disgust. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:22.1":{"pli":"Chuddhūna naṃ susāne, ","eng":"When they’ve discarded it in the charnel ground, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:22.2":{"pli":"Parabhattaṃ nhāyanti jigucchantā; ","eng":"to be eaten by others, your own parents ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:22.3":{"pli":"Niyakā mātāpitaro, ","eng":"bathe themselves, disgusted; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:22.4":{"pli":"Kiṃ pana sādhāraṇā janatā. ","eng":"what then of people at large? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:23.1":{"pli":"Ajjhositā asāre, ","eng":"They’re attached to this hollow carcass, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:23.2":{"pli":"Kaḷevare aṭṭhinhārusaṅghāte; ","eng":"this mass of sinews and bone; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:23.3":{"pli":"Kheḷassuccārassava, ","eng":"this rotting body ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:23.4":{"pli":"Paripuṇṇe pūtikāyamhi. ","eng":"full of saliva, tears, feces, and pus. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:24.1":{"pli":"Yo naṃ vinibbhujitvā, ","eng":"If anyone were to dissect it, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:24.2":{"pli":"Abbhantaramassa bāhiraṃ kayirā; ","eng":"turning it inside out, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:24.3":{"pli":"Gandhassa asahamānā, ","eng":"the unbearable stench ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:24.4":{"pli":"Sakāpi mātā jiguccheyya. ","eng":"would disgust even their own mother. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:25.1":{"pli":"Khandhadhātuāyatanaṃ, ","eng":"Rationally examining ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:25.2":{"pli":"Saṅkhataṃ jātimūlakaṃ dukkhaṃ; ","eng":"the aggregates, elements, and sense fields ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:25.3":{"pli":"Yoniso anuvicinantī, ","eng":"as conditioned, rooted in birth, suffering—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:25.4":{"pli":"Vāreyyaṃ kissa iccheyyaṃ. ","eng":"why would I wish for marriage? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:26.1":{"pli":"Divase divase tisatti, ","eng":"Let three hundred sharp swords ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:26.2":{"pli":"Satāni navanavā pateyyuṃ kāyamhi; ","eng":"fall on my body everyday! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:26.3":{"pli":"Vassasatampi ca ghāto, ","eng":"Even if the slaughter lasted a hundred years ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:26.4":{"pli":"Seyyo dukkhassa cevaṃ khayo. ","eng":"it’d be worth it if it led to the end of suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:27.1":{"pli":"Ajjhupagacche ghātaṃ, ","eng":"One who understands the Teacher’s words ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:27.2":{"pli":"Yo viññāyevaṃ satthuno vacanaṃ; ","eng":"would put up with this slaughter: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:27.3":{"pli":"‘Dīgho tesaṃ saṃsāro, ","eng":"‘Long for you is transmigration ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:27.4":{"pli":"Punappunaṃ haññamānānaṃ’. ","eng":"being killed time and time again.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:28.1":{"pli":"Devesu manussesu ca, ","eng":"Among gods and humans, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:28.2":{"pli":"Tiracchānayoniyā asurakāye; ","eng":"in the realm of animals or that of titans, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:28.3":{"pli":"Petesu ca nirayesu ca, ","eng":"among the ghosts or in the hells, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:28.4":{"pli":"Aparimitā dissare ghātā. ","eng":"endless killings are seen. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:29.1":{"pli":"Ghātā nirayesu bahū, ","eng":"The hells are full of killing, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:29.2":{"pli":"Vinipātagatassa pīḷiyamānassa; ","eng":"for the corrupt who have fallen to the underworld. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:29.3":{"pli":"Devesupi attāṇaṃ, ","eng":"Even among the gods there is no shelter, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:29.4":{"pli":"Nibbānasukhā paraṃ natthi. ","eng":"for no happiness excels extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:30.1":{"pli":"Pattā te nibbānaṃ, ","eng":"Those who are committed to the dispensation ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:30.2":{"pli":"Ye yuttā dasabalassa pāvacane; ","eng":"of him of the ten powers attain extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:30.3":{"pli":"Appossukkā ghaṭenti, ","eng":"Living at ease, they apply themselves ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:30.4":{"pli":"Jātimaraṇappahānāya. ","eng":"to giving up rebirth and death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:31.1":{"pli":"Ajjeva tātabhinikkha- ","eng":"On this very day, dad, I shall renounce: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:31.2":{"pli":"Missaṃ bhogehi kiṃ asārehi; ","eng":"what’s to enjoy in hollow riches? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:31.3":{"pli":"Nibbinnā me kāmā, ","eng":"I’m disillusioned with sensual pleasures, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:31.4":{"pli":"Vantasamā tālavatthukatā”. ","eng":"they’re like vomit, made like a palm stump.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:32.1":{"pli":"Sā cevaṃ bhaṇati pitara- ","eng":"As she spoke thus to her father, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:32.2":{"pli":"Manīkaratto ca yassa sā dinnā; ","eng":"Anīkaratta, to whom she was betrothed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:32.3":{"pli":"Upayāsi vāraṇavate, ","eng":"approached from Vāraṇavatī ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:32.4":{"pli":"Vāreyyamupaṭṭhite kāle. ","eng":"at the time appointed for the marriage. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:33.1":{"pli":"Atha asitanicitamuduke, ","eng":"Then Sumedhā took up a knife, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:33.2":{"pli":"Kese khaggena chindiya sumedhā; ","eng":"and cut off her hair, so black, thick, and soft. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:33.3":{"pli":"Pāsādaṃ pidahitvā, ","eng":"Shutting herself in the longhouse, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:33.4":{"pli":"Paṭhamajjhānaṃ samāpajji. ","eng":"she entered the first absorption. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:34.1":{"pli":"Sā ca tahiṃ samāpannā, ","eng":"And as she entered it there, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:34.2":{"pli":"Anīkaratto ca āgato nagaraṃ; ","eng":"Anīkaratta arrived at the city. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:34.3":{"pli":"Pāsāde ca sumedhā, ","eng":"Then in the longhouse, Sumedhā ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:34.4":{"pli":"Aniccasaññaṃ subhāveti. ","eng":"well developed the perception of impermanence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:35.1":{"pli":"Sā ca manasi karoti, ","eng":"As she investigated in meditation, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:35.2":{"pli":"Anīkaratto ca āruhī turitaṃ; ","eng":"Anīkaratta quickly climbed the stairs. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:35.3":{"pli":"Maṇikanakabhūsitaṅgo, ","eng":"His limbs adorned with gems <j>and honey-yellow gold, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:35.4":{"pli":"Katañjalī yācati sumedhaṃ. ","eng":"he begged Sumedhā with joined palms: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:36.1":{"pli":"“Rajje āṇādhanamissa- ","eng":"“As a royal there is command, wealth, authority, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:36.2":{"pli":"Riyaṃ bhogā sukhā daharikāsi; ","eng":"and the happiness of possessions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:36.3":{"pli":"Bhuñjāhi kāmabhoge, ","eng":"Enjoy sensual pleasures while you’re still young! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:36.4":{"pli":"Kāmasukhā dullabhā loke. ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are hard to find in the world! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:37.1":{"pli":"Nissaṭṭhaṃ te rajjaṃ, ","eng":"I’ve handed royalty to you—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:37.2":{"pli":"Bhoge bhuñjassu dehi dānāni; ","eng":"enjoy riches, give gifts! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:37.3":{"pli":"Mā dummanā ahosi, ","eng":"Don’t be sad; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:37.4":{"pli":"Mātāpitaro te dukkhitā”. ","eng":"your parents are upset.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:38.1":{"pli":"Taṃ taṃ bhaṇati sumedhā, ","eng":"Sumedhā, having no use for sensual pleasures, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:38.2":{"pli":"Kāmehi anatthikā vigatamohā; ","eng":"and having done away with delusion, <j>spoke right back: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:38.3":{"pli":"“Mā kāme abhinandi, ","eng":"“Do not take pleasure in sensuality! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:38.4":{"pli":"Kāmesvādīnavaṃ passa. ","eng":"See the danger in sensual pleasures! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:39.1":{"pli":"Cātuddīpo rājā, ","eng":"Mandhātā, king of four continents, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:39.2":{"pli":"Mandhātā āsi kāmabhoginamaggo; ","eng":"foremost in enjoying sensual pleasures, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:39.3":{"pli":"Atitto kālaṅkato, ","eng":"died unsated, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:39.4":{"pli":"Na cassa paripūritā icchā. ","eng":"his desires unfulfilled. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:40.1":{"pli":"Satta ratanāni vasseyya, ","eng":"Were the seven jewels to rain from the sky ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:40.2":{"pli":"Vuṭṭhimā dasadisā samantena; ","eng":"all over the ten directions, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:40.3":{"pli":"Na catthi titti kāmānaṃ, ","eng":"there would be no sating of sensual pleasures: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:40.4":{"pli":"Atittāva maranti narā. ","eng":"people die insatiable. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:41.1":{"pli":"Asisūnūpamā kāmā, ","eng":"Like a butcher’s knife and chopping board, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:41.2":{"pli":"kāmā sappasiropamā; ","eng":"sensual pleasures are like a snake’s head. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:41.3":{"pli":"Ukkopamā anudahanti, ","eng":"They burn like a fire-brand, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:41.4":{"pli":"aṭṭhikaṅkala sannibhā. ","eng":"they resemble a skeleton. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:42.1":{"pli":"Aniccā adhuvā kāmā, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are impermanent and unstable, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:42.2":{"pli":"bahudukkhā mahāvisā; ","eng":"they’re full of suffering, a terrible poison; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:42.3":{"pli":"Ayoguḷova santatto, ","eng":"like a hot iron ball, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:42.4":{"pli":"aghamūlā dukhapphalā. ","eng":"the root of gloom, their fruit is pain. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:43.1":{"pli":"Rukkhapphalūpamā kāmā, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are like fruits of a tree, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:43.2":{"pli":"maṃsapesūpamā dukhā; ","eng":"like scraps of meat, painful, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:43.3":{"pli":"Supinopamā vañcaniyā, ","eng":"they trick you like a dream; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:43.4":{"pli":"kāmā yācitakūpamā. ","eng":"sensual pleasures are like borrowed goods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:44.1":{"pli":"Sattisūlūpamā kāmā, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are like swords and spears; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:44.2":{"pli":"rogo gaṇḍo aghaṃ nighaṃ; ","eng":"a disease, a boil, gloom and trouble. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:44.3":{"pli":"Aṅgārakāsusadisā, ","eng":"Like a pit of glowing coals, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:44.4":{"pli":"aghamūlaṃ bhayaṃ vadho. ","eng":"the root of gloom, fear and slaughter. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:45.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ bahudukkhā kāmā, ","eng":"Thus sensual pleasures have been explained ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:45.2":{"pli":"akkhātā antarāyikā; ","eng":"to be obstructions, so full of suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:45.3":{"pli":"Gacchatha na me bhavagate, ","eng":"Please leave! As for me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:45.4":{"pli":"vissāso atthi attano. ","eng":"I have no trust in any state of life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:46.1":{"pli":"Kiṃ mama paro karissati, ","eng":"What can someone else do for me ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:46.2":{"pli":"Attano sīsamhi ḍayhamānamhi; ","eng":"when their own head is burning? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:46.3":{"pli":"Anubandhe jarāmaraṇe, ","eng":"When stalked by old age and death, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:46.4":{"pli":"Tassa ghātāya ghaṭitabbaṃ”. ","eng":"you should strive to destroy them.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:47.1":{"pli":"Dvāraṃ apāpuritvānahaṃ, ","eng":"She opened the door ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:47.2":{"pli":"Mātāpitaro anīkarattañca; ","eng":"and saw her parents with Anīkaratta, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:47.3":{"pli":"Disvāna chamaṃ nisinne, ","eng":"sitting crying on the floor. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:47.4":{"pli":"Rodante idamavocaṃ. ","eng":"And so she said this: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:48.1":{"pli":"“Dīgho bālānaṃ saṃsāro, ","eng":"“Transmigration is long for fools, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:48.2":{"pli":"Punappunañca rodataṃ; ","eng":"crying again and again <j>at that with no known beginning—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:48.3":{"pli":"Anamatagge pitu maraṇe, ","eng":"the death of a father, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:48.4":{"pli":"Bhātu vadhe attano ca vadhe. ","eng":"the killing of a brother or of themselves. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:49.1":{"pli":"Assu thaññaṃ rudhiraṃ, ","eng":"Remember the ocean of tears, of milk, of blood—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:49.2":{"pli":"Saṃsāraṃ anamataggato saratha; ","eng":"transmigration with no known beginning. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:49.3":{"pli":"Sattānaṃ saṃsarataṃ, ","eng":"Remember the bones piled up ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:49.4":{"pli":"Sarāhi aṭṭhīnañca sannicayaṃ. ","eng":"by beings transmigrating. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:50.1":{"pli":"Sara caturodadhī, ","eng":"Remember the four oceans ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:50.2":{"pli":"Upanīte assuthaññarudhiramhi; ","eng":"compared with tears, milk, and blood. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:50.3":{"pli":"Sara ekakappamaṭṭhīnaṃ, ","eng":"Remember bones piled up high as Mount Vipula ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:50.4":{"pli":"Sañcayaṃ vipulena samaṃ. ","eng":"in the course of a single eon. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:51.1":{"pli":"Anamatagge saṃsarato, ","eng":"Transmigration with no known beginning ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:51.2":{"pli":"Mahiṃ jambudīpamupanītaṃ; ","eng":"is compared to this broad Black Plum Tree Land; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:51.3":{"pli":"Kolaṭṭhimattaguḷikā, ","eng":"if divided into lumps the size of jujube seeds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:51.4":{"pli":"Mātā mātusveva nappahonti. ","eng":"they’d still be fewer than his mother’s mothers. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:52.1":{"pli":"Tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ, ","eng":"Remember the grass, sticks, and leaves, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:52.2":{"pli":"Upanītaṃ anamataggato sara; ","eng":"compare that with no known beginning: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:52.3":{"pli":"Caturaṅgulikā ghaṭikā, ","eng":"if split into chips four inches in size, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:52.4":{"pli":"Pitupitusveva nappahonti. ","eng":"they’d still be fewer than his father’s fathers. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:53.1":{"pli":"Sara kāṇakacchapaṃ pubba- ","eng":"Remember the one-eyed turtle <j>and the yoke with a hole ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:53.2":{"pli":"Samudde aparato ca yugachiddaṃ; ","eng":"blown in the ocean from east to west—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:53.3":{"pli":"Siraṃ tassa ca paṭimukkaṃ, ","eng":"sticking the head in the hole ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:53.4":{"pli":"Manussalābhamhi opammaṃ. ","eng":"is a metaphor for gaining a human birth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:54.1":{"pli":"Sara rūpaṃ pheṇapiṇḍopa- ","eng":"Remember the form of this unlucky body, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:54.2":{"pli":"Massa kāyakalino asārassa; ","eng":"insubstantial as a lump of foam. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"A reference to <a href='index.html?q=sn22.95#2.1'>SN 22.95:2.1</a>. "},"thig16.1:54.3":{"pli":"Khandhe passa anicce, ","eng":"See the aggregates as impermanent, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:54.4":{"pli":"Sarāhi niraye bahuvighāte. ","eng":"remember the hells so full of distress. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:55.1":{"pli":"Sara kaṭasiṃ vaḍḍhente, ","eng":"Remember those swelling the charnel grounds ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:55.2":{"pli":"Punappunaṃ tāsu tāsu jātīsu; ","eng":"again and again in life after life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:55.3":{"pli":"Sara kumbhīlabhayāni ca, ","eng":"Remember the danger of gharials! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"A reference to the metaphor for gluttony at <a href='index.html?q=mn67#17.1'>MN 67:17.1</a> and <a href='index.html?q=an4.122#3.1'>AN 4.122:3.1</a>. "},"thig16.1:55.4":{"pli":"Sarāhi cattāri saccāni. ","eng":"Remember the four truths! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:56.1":{"pli":"Amatamhi vijjamāne, ","eng":"When freedom from death is there to be found, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:56.2":{"pli":"Kiṃ tava pañcakaṭukena pītena; ","eng":"why would you drink the five bitter poisons? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:56.3":{"pli":"Sabbā hi kāmaratiyo, ","eng":"For all erotic delights ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:56.4":{"pli":"Kaṭukatarā pañcakaṭukena. ","eng":"are so much more bitter than them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:57.1":{"pli":"Amatamhi vijjamāne, ","eng":"When freedom from death is there to be found, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:57.2":{"pli":"Kiṃ tava kāmehi ye pariḷāhā; ","eng":"why would you burn for sensual pleasures? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:57.3":{"pli":"Sabbā hi kāmaratiyo, ","eng":"For all erotic delights ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:57.4":{"pli":"Jalitā kuthitā kampitā santāpitā. ","eng":"are burning, boiling, bubbling, seething. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:58.1":{"pli":"Asapattamhi samāne, ","eng":"When there is freedom from enmity, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:58.2":{"pli":"Kiṃ tava kāmehi ye bahusapattā; ","eng":"why would you want your enemy, sensual pleasures? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:58.3":{"pli":"Rājaggicoraudakappiyehi, ","eng":"Many enemies take a share of your sensual pleasures: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The same sense is expressed in prose at <a href='index.html?q=an5.227#1.3'>AN 5.227:1.3</a>. "},"thig16.1:58.4":{"pli":"Sādhāraṇā kāmā bahusapattā. ","eng":"kings, fire, robbers, flood, and unloved heirs. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:59.1":{"pli":"Mokkhamhi vijjamāne, ","eng":"When liberation is there to be found, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:59.2":{"pli":"Kiṃ tava kāmehi yesu vadhabandho; ","eng":"what good are sensual pleasures that kill and bind? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:59.3":{"pli":"Kāmesu hi asakāmā, ","eng":"For though unwilling, <j>when sensual pleasures are there, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:59.4":{"pli":"Vadhabandhadukhāni anubhonti. ","eng":"they are subject to the pain of killing and binding. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:60.1":{"pli":"Ādīpitā tiṇukkā, ","eng":"As a blazing grass torch ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:60.2":{"pli":"Gaṇhantaṃ dahanti neva muñcantaṃ; ","eng":"burns one who grasps it without letting go, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:60.3":{"pli":"Ukkopamā hi kāmā, ","eng":"sensual pleasures are like a grass torch, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:60.4":{"pli":"Dahanti ye te na muñcanti. ","eng":"burning those who do not let go. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:61.1":{"pli":"Mā appakassa hetu, ","eng":"Don’t give up abundant happiness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:61.2":{"pli":"Kāmasukhassa vipulaṃ jahī sukhaṃ; ","eng":"for the trivial joys of sensual pleasure. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:61.3":{"pli":"Mā puthulomova baḷisaṃ, ","eng":"Don’t fret later, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:61.4":{"pli":"Gilitvā pacchā vihaññasi. ","eng":"like a catfish on a hook. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:62.1":{"pli":"Kāmaṃ kāmesu damassu, ","eng":"Deliberately control yourself <j>among sensual pleasures! ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:62.2":{"pli":"Tāva sunakhova saṅkhalābaddho; ","eng":"You’re like a hound fixed to a chain: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:62.3":{"pli":"Kāhinti khu taṃ kāmā, ","eng":"sensual pleasures will surely devour you ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:62.4":{"pli":"Chātā sunakhaṃva caṇḍālā. ","eng":"as hungry corpse-workers would a dog. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:63.1":{"pli":"Aparimitañca dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Harnessed to sensual pleasure, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:63.2":{"pli":"Bahūni ca cittadomanassāni; ","eng":"you undergo endless pain, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:63.3":{"pli":"Anubhohisi kāmayutto, ","eng":"along with much mental anguish: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:63.4":{"pli":"Paṭinissaja addhuve kāme. ","eng":"relinquish sensual pleasures, they don’t last! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:64.1":{"pli":"Ajaramhi vijjamāne, ","eng":"When the unaging is there to be found, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:64.2":{"pli":"Kiṃ tava kāmehi yesu jarā; ","eng":"what good are sensual pleasures in which is old age? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:64.3":{"pli":"Maraṇabyādhigahitā, ","eng":"All rebirths everywhere ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:64.4":{"pli":"Sabbā sabbattha jātiyo. ","eng":"are bonded to death and sickness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:65.1":{"pli":"Idamajaramidamamaraṃ, ","eng":"This is freedom from old age, freedom from death! ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:65.2":{"pli":"Idamajarāmaraṃ padamasokaṃ; ","eng":"This is freedom from old age and death, the sorrowless state! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:65.3":{"pli":"Asapattamasambādhaṃ, ","eng":"Free of enmity, unconstricted, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:65.4":{"pli":"Akhalitamabhayaṃ nirupatāpaṃ. ","eng":"faultless, fearless, without tribulations. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:66.1":{"pli":"Adhigatamidaṃ bahūhi, ","eng":"This freedom from death has been realized by many; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:66.2":{"pli":"Amataṃ ajjāpi ca labhanīyamidaṃ; ","eng":"even today it can be obtained ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:66.3":{"pli":"Yo yoniso payuñjati, ","eng":"by those who rationally apply themselves; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:66.4":{"pli":"Na ca sakkā aghaṭamānena”. ","eng":"but it’s impossible if you don’t try.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:67.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ bhaṇati sumedhā, ","eng":"So said Sumedhā, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:67.2":{"pli":"Saṅkhāragate ratiṃ alabhamānā; ","eng":"lacking delight in conditioned things. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:67.3":{"pli":"Anunentī anikarattaṃ, ","eng":"Soothing Anīkaratta, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:67.4":{"pli":"Kese ca chamaṃ khipi sumedhā. ","eng":"Sumedhā cast her hair on the ground. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:68.1":{"pli":"Uṭṭhāya anikaratto, ","eng":"Standing up, Anīkaratta ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:68.2":{"pli":"Pañjaliko yācatassā pitaraṃ so; ","eng":"raised his joined palms to her father and begged: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:68.3":{"pli":"“Vissajjetha sumedhaṃ, ","eng":"“Let go of Sumedhā, so that she may go forth! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:68.4":{"pli":"Pabbajituṃ vimokkhasaccadassā”. ","eng":"She will see the truth of liberation.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:69.1":{"pli":"Vissajjitā mātāpitūhi, ","eng":"Released by her mother and father, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:69.2":{"pli":"pabbaji sokabhayabhītā; ","eng":"she went forth, afraid of grief and fear. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:69.3":{"pli":"Cha abhiññā sacchikatā, ","eng":"While still a trainee nun <j>she realized the six direct knowledges, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:69.4":{"pli":"aggaphalaṃ sikkhamānāya. ","eng":"along with the highest fruit. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:70.1":{"pli":"Acchariyamabbhutaṃ taṃ, ","eng":"The extinguishment of the princess ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:70.2":{"pli":"Nibbānaṃ āsi rājakaññāya; ","eng":"was incredible and amazing; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:70.3":{"pli":"Pubbenivāsacaritaṃ, ","eng":"on her deathbed, she declared ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:70.4":{"pli":"Yathā byākari pacchime kāle. ","eng":"her several past lives. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:71.1":{"pli":"“Bhagavati koṇāgamane, ","eng":"“In the time of the Buddha Koṇāgamana, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:71.2":{"pli":"Saṅghārāmamhi navanivesamhi; ","eng":"we three friends gave the gift ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:71.3":{"pli":"Sakhiyo tisso janiyo, ","eng":"of a newly-built dwelling ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:71.4":{"pli":"Vihāradānaṃ adāsimha. ","eng":"in the Saṅgha’s monastery. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:72.1":{"pli":"Dasakkhattuṃ satakkhattuṃ, ","eng":"Ten times, a hundred times, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:72.2":{"pli":"Dasasatakkhattuṃ satāni ca satakkhattuṃ; ","eng":"a thousand times, ten thousand times, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:72.3":{"pli":"Devesu uppajjimha, ","eng":"we were reborn among the gods, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:72.4":{"pli":"Ko pana vādo manussesu. ","eng":"let alone among humans. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:73.1":{"pli":"Devesu mahiddhikā ahumha, ","eng":"We were mighty among the gods, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:73.2":{"pli":"Mānusakamhi ko pana vādo; ","eng":"let alone among humans! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:73.3":{"pli":"Sattaratanassa mahesī, ","eng":"I was queen to a king with the seven treasures—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:73.4":{"pli":"Itthiratanaṃ ahaṃ āsiṃ. ","eng":"I was the treasure of a wife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:74.1":{"pli":"So hetu so pabhavo, ","eng":"That was the cause, that the origin, that the root, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:74.2":{"pli":"Taṃ mūlaṃ sāva sāsane khantī; ","eng":"that was the acceptance of the dispensation; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:74.3":{"pli":"Taṃ paṭhamasamodhānaṃ, ","eng":"that first meeting culminated in extinguishment ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:74.4":{"pli":"Taṃ dhammaratāya nibbānaṃ. ","eng":"for one delighting in the teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig16.1:75.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ karonti ye sadda- ","eng":"So say those who have faith in the words ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:75.2":{"pli":"Hanti vacanaṃ anomapaññassa; ","eng":"of the one unrivaled in wisdom. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:75.3":{"pli":"Nibbindanti bhavagate, ","eng":"They’re disillusioned with any state of life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:75.4":{"pli":"Nibbinditvā virajjantī”ti. ","eng":"and being disillusioned they become dispassionate.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig16.1:76.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ sumedhā therī gāthāyo abhāsitthāti. ","eng":"That is how these verses were recited by the senior nun Sumedhā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig16.1:76.2":{"pli":"Mahānipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'><a class='sc'></a>{}</p>"},"thig16.1:77.0":{"pli":"Samattā therīgāthāyo ","html":"<p class='uddana-intro'><a class='sc'></a>{}</p>"},"thig16.1:77.1":{"pli":"Gāthāsatāni cattāri, ","html":"<blockquote class='uddanagatha'><p><a class='sc'></a><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:77.2":{"pli":"asīti puna cuddasa; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:77.3":{"pli":"Theriyekuttarasatā, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig16.1:77.4":{"pli":"sabbā tā āsavakkhayāti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig16.1:77.5":{"pli":"Therīgāthāpāḷi niṭṭhitā. ","eng":"The Verses of the Senior Nuns are finished. ","html":"<p class='endbook'><a class='sc'></a>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.1":{"thig2.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.1 ","html":"<article id='thig2.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.1:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.1:0.3":{"pli":"Abhirūpanandātherīgāthā ","eng":"Abhirūpanandā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Āturaṃ asuciṃ pūtiṃ, ","eng":"Nandā, see this bag of bones as ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:1.2":{"pli":"passa nande samussayaṃ; ","eng":"diseased, filthy, and rotten. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:1.3":{"pli":"Asubhāya cittaṃ bhāvehi, ","eng":"With mind unified and serene, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:1.4":{"pli":"ekaggaṃ susamāhitaṃ. ","eng":"meditate on the ugly aspects of the body. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.1:2.1":{"pli":"Animittañca bhāvehi, ","eng":"Meditate on the signless, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:2.2":{"pli":"mānānusayamujjaha; ","eng":"give up the tendency to conceit; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:2.3":{"pli":"Tato mānābhisamayā, ","eng":"and when you comprehend conceit, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.1:2.4":{"pli":"upasantā carissasī”ti. ","eng":"you will live at peace. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.1:3.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ abhirūpanandā therī gāthāyo abhāsitthāti. ","eng":"That is how the Buddha regularly advised the trainee nun Nandā with these verses. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>","comm":"The MS edition is apparently alone in taking the nun as a bhikkhunī and as the speaker of the verses. It’s odd that no variants are recorded, especially given that even the parent edition (VRI) says she is a <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sikkhamānā</i>. Perhaps this is a rare instance of a simple oversight in MS. "}}}